When a company incurs a debt that they feel won't be collected on, they have two options: 1. Write the debt off as a "Total Loss," and write it off the books for a tax credit. These are collections. Here's how it works: The Hospital (or whoever) SELLS that $10,000 outstanding debt to Bergstein & Bergstein for $500 cash.
